radiographic_examinations.findings: Small bilateral pleural effusions, basilar atelectasis more prominent on the left, a 25 mm simple cyst in the right kidney, diffuse thickening of the second, third, and fourth portions of the duodenum, ileus in proximal small bowel loops measuring up to 3.7 cm, moderate amount of ascites, peripancreatic fluid collection with extension into the left paracolic gutter, and diffuse mesenteric haziness and nodularity in the left upper quadrant.
